          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-10-14 12:48:10.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-9040 ofd: keep orphan OST-objects conditionally",
        "message": "LU-9040 ofd: keep orphan OST-objects conditionally\n\nSometimes, after the first osp_precreate_cleanup_orphans(),\nthe MDS may lost some precreate RPC replies because of network\ntrouble or some unknown reasons. Then the MDS will not know\nthe lastest LAST_ID. That will misguide the OST to regard the\nMDS corruption and refuse the MDS to precreate. To avoid such\ntrouble, the MDS will set the flag OBD_FL_KEEPORPHAN for the\nnon-first osp_precreate_cleanup_orphans() to tell OST to keep\norphan OST-objects if such case happened.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I158c33c85f862a2521dc34b3ff926ba6ed1ecfc7\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
